ShortName: Decision trees
Topic: statistical-learning
Concepts: recursive binary splitting (greedily choose the predictor and cutpoint that minimize RSS or impurity),
 terminal nodes (leaves) as the prediction regions,
 the Gini index as the split criterion for classification,
 cost-complexity pruning (grow big then cut back with a penalty on tree size),
 trees vs linear models (axis-aligned rectangles vs linear boundaries),
 tree instability (small data changes can produce very different trees)
BuildsOn: [model-fit-error-and-validation](model-fit-error-and-validation/lesson.qmd),
 [classification-evaluation](classification-evaluation/lesson.qmd)
UsedBy: —
